CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 18, 1970, pg. 18, reads: "NAACP Life Membership - Members of the Swan Civic Club gave a recent Cocktail Party at the Night Cap East at which time they presented a check as payment on a Life Membership in NAACP. Presentation was made to singer Tim Stevens, coordinator for the NAACP Youth Council of Pittsburgh.  Pictured left to right: Maxine Holman, social chairman;  Dorothy Phillips, sergeant-at-arms; Margaret Twyman, secretary; Deloris Fields, treasurer; Tim Stevens; Nellie Cathie, president (presenting check); Juanita Walker, hospitality chairman; Lois Washington and Rose Cowart, financial secretary.  Looking on (center background) Donna Phillips attractive hostess for the evening. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of Swan Civic League, from left: Maxine Holman, Dorothy Phillips, Margaret Twyman, Deloris Fields, Tim Stevens, Donna Phillips, Nellie Cathie holding check for NAACP, Juanita Walker, Lois Washington, and Rose Cowart, posed in Night Cap East
